      <c01 level="series">
        <did>
          <unittitle>Writings, sermons, and addresses</unittitle>
        </did>
        <scopecontent>
          <p>The Writings, sermons, and addresses series is largely arranged chronologically and contains speeches that Emrich made while Bishop of Michigan. The occasion for these speeches were varied and were often given to groups outside of the church, although the majority of them have a religious theme. Also in this series are a set of addresses pertaining to civil rights as well as a copy of his Reinecker Lectures (an annual lecture series of the Theological Seminary of Alexandria, Virginia) of 1951. The sermons were preached by Emrich on different occasions. Many of these sermons were for ordination ceremonies and holidays.</p>
        </scopecontent>
